title: Avocado Toast with Poached Eggs
description: Sourdough toast topped with smashed avocado, poached eggs, and red pepper flakes.
steps: Toast sourdough slices until golden.
Bring water to a gentle simmer, add a splash of vinegar, and poach eggs for 3-4 minutes.
Mash avocado onto toast, top with eggs, and season with salt and pepper flakes.

title: Greek Yogurt with Berries and Walnuts
description: Creamy full-fat Greek yogurt topped with fresh berries, walnuts, and raw honey.
steps: Spoon yogurt into a bowl.
Top with berries and walnuts.
Drizzle with raw honey.

title: Banana Almond Butter Smoothie
description: Thick, creamy smoothie with banana, almond butter, and cinnamon.
steps: Add all ingredients to a blender.
Blend on high until smooth and creamy.
Pour and enjoy immediately.

title: Overnight Oats with Chia Seeds
description: Steel-cut oats soaked overnight with chia seeds, topped with fresh fruit.
steps: Combine oats, chia seeds, almond milk, and maple syrup in a jar.
Stir well, cover, and refrigerate overnight.
Top with blueberries before eating.

title: Scrambled Eggs with Spinach and Tomato
description: Fluffy eggs scrambled with fresh spinach, cherry tomatoes, cooked in butter.
steps: Melt butter in a skillet over medium-low heat.
Halve tomatoes and sauté for 1 minute, add spinach and wilt.
Pour in beaten eggs, stir gently until soft curds form. Season and serve.

title: Sweet Potato and Egg Hash
description: Cubed sweet potato pan-fried with onion, topped with a fried egg.
steps: Dice sweet potato into small cubes; dice onion.
Heat olive oil, cook sweet potato 8-10 minutes until tender, add onion last 2 minutes.
Fry eggs in the same pan, serve atop hash with paprika.

title: Coconut Flour Pancakes
description: Grain-free pancakes made with coconut flour, eggs, and banana.
steps: Mash banana and whisk with eggs and vanilla.
Stir in coconut flour until smooth batter forms.
Cook on a coconut-oil-greased skillet, 2-3 minutes per side.

title: Smoked Salmon and Cream Cheese on Rye
description: Whole-grain rye bread with wild-caught smoked salmon, cream cheese, and capers.
steps: Toast rye bread lightly.
Spread cream cheese, lay salmon slices on top.
Garnish with capers and dill.

title: Tropical Fruit Bowl
description: Fresh mango, pineapple, and kiwi topped with shredded coconut and hemp seeds.
steps: Peel and dice mango and kiwi; cut pineapple into chunks.
Arrange fruit in a bowl.
Sprinkle with coconut and hemp seeds.

title: Egg and Veggie Muffin Cups
description: Baked egg cups with bell pepper, mushroom, and fresh herbs.
steps: Preheat oven to 375°F. Grease a muffin tin with olive oil.
Dice pepper and mushrooms; distribute evenly among 6 cups.
Beat eggs with chives, pour over vegetables. Bake 15 minutes.

title: Mediterranean Quinoa Bowl
description: Quinoa with roasted vegetables, chickpeas, olive oil, lemon tahini dressing.
steps: Cook quinoa per package directions and let cool slightly.
Drain and rinse chickpeas; dice cucumber; halve tomatoes.
Whisk tahini, lemon juice, and olive oil for dressing.
Toss everything together and serve.

title: Grilled Chicken Caesar Salad
description: Romaine lettuce with grilled chicken, parmesan, and homemade Caesar dressing.
steps: Season chicken with salt and pepper; grill 5 minutes per side until cooked through.
Chop romaine and shave parmesan.
Whisk olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, and mustard for dressing.
Slice chicken, arrange over lettuce, drizzle dressing and top with parmesan.

title: Black Bean and Sweet Potato Tacos
description: Warm corn tortillas filled with roasted sweet potato, black beans, and avocado.
steps: Dice sweet potato; roast at 400°F with olive oil and cumin for 15 minutes.
Warm black beans in a small pot; warm tortillas.
Fill tortillas with sweet potato, beans, sliced avocado, and a squeeze of lime.

title: Tuna Salad Lettuce Wraps
description: Wild-caught tuna mixed with avocado, celery, and lemon in butter lettuce cups.
steps: Drain tuna; mash avocado and mix with tuna.
Dice celery and fold in; add lemon juice, salt, and pepper.
Spoon into lettuce leaves and serve.

title: Roasted Beet and Goat Cheese Salad
description: Earthy roasted beets with tangy goat cheese, arugula, and walnuts.
steps: Slice beets into wedges.
Toss arugula with olive oil and vinegar.
Top with beets, crumbled goat cheese, and walnuts.

title: Turkey and Avocado Collard Wrap
description: Sliced turkey breast wrapped in collard greens with avocado and mustard.
steps: Trim thick stems from collard leaves; blanch 30 seconds and pat dry.
Spread mustard on leaves, layer turkey, avocado slices, and tomato.
Roll tightly, slice in half, and serve.

title: Lentil Soup
description: Hearty red lentil soup with cumin, turmeric, and a squeeze of lemon.
steps: Sauté diced onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add cumin and turmeric; stir 30 seconds.
Add lentils and broth; simmer 18-20 minutes until lentils are tender.
Season with salt and lemon juice. Blend partially for creaminess if desired.

title: Shrimp and Mango Salad
description: Grilled shrimp with ripe mango, red onion, cilantro, and lime dressing.
steps: Season shrimp with salt; grill or pan-sear 2 minutes per side.
Dice mango and thinly slice red onion.
Toss everything with lime juice, olive oil, and cilantro.

title: Chicken and Vegetable Stir-Fry
description: Chicken breast stir-fried with broccoli, snap peas, and coconut aminos.
steps: Slice chicken thin; stir-fry in coconut oil 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and snap peas; cook 3-4 minutes.
Add ginger and coconut aminos; toss and serve.

title: Caprese Stuffed Avocado
description: Halved avocados filled with fresh mozzarella, tomato, and basil.
steps: Halve and pit avocados.
Dice mozzarella and tomato; tear basil.
Fill avocado halves with mixture; drizzle with balsamic.

title: Grilled Salmon with Asparagus
description: Wild-caught salmon fillet with roasted asparagus and lemon.
steps: Preheat oven to 400°F. Trim asparagus.
Place salmon and asparagus on a baking sheet; drizzle with olive oil, minced garlic, lemon juice.
Bake 12-15 minutes until salmon flakes easily.

title: Grass-Fed Beef Burgers (Lettuce Wrap)
description: Juicy grass-fed beef patty in a lettuce wrap with tomato and pickles.
steps: Form beef into 2 patties; season with salt and pepper.
Grill or pan-sear 4-5 minutes per side.
Wrap in lettuce leaves with tomato, pickles, and mustard.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp with Zucchini Noodles
description: Sautéed shrimp in garlic and butter over spiralized zucchini.
steps: Spiralize zucchini into noodles.
Melt butter, sauté minced garlic 30 seconds, add shrimp and cook 2-3 min per side.
Toss in zucchini noodles for 1 minute; finish with lemon juice and parsley.

title: One-Pan Chicken Thighs with Root Vegetables
description: Bone-in chicken thighs roasted with carrots, parsnips, and rosemary.
steps: Preheat oven to 425°F. Cut carrots and parsnips into chunks.
Toss vegetables with olive oil; nestle chicken thighs among them.
Season with salt, pepper, rosemary. Roast 25-30 minutes.

title: Cauliflower Fried Rice
description: Riced cauliflower stir-fried with egg, peas, carrot, and coconut aminos.
steps: Rice cauliflower in a food processor.
Scramble eggs in sesame oil; set aside.
Stir-fry diced carrot and peas 2 min, add cauliflower rice 3 min.
Add coconut aminos and egg; toss with sliced green onions.

title: Baked Cod with Tomatoes and Olives
description: Flaky cod baked in a bed of cherry tomatoes, Kalamata olives, and herbs.
steps: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Arrange tomatoes, olives, and capers in baking dish; nestle cod on top.
Drizzle with olive oil; season and sprinkle oregano. Bake 15-18 minutes.

title: Turkey Meatballs with Marinara
description: Tender ground turkey meatballs in homemade tomato sauce with fresh basil.
steps: Mix turkey, almond flour, egg, minced garlic, salt, and pepper. Form into balls.
Brown meatballs in olive oil on all sides.
Add crushed tomatoes; simmer covered 15 minutes.
Finish with torn basil leaves.

title: Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: Bell peppers filled with ground beef, cauliflower rice, and tomato sauce.
steps: Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Brown beef with garlic and cumin; mix in cauliflower rice and half the tomato sauce.
Stuff peppers, top with remaining sauce, and bake at 375°F for 20 minutes.

title: Herb-Crusted Roast Chicken
description: Whole chicken roasted with fresh herbs, garlic, and root vegetables.
steps: Preheat oven to 425°F. Pat chicken dry and rub with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Stuff cavity with halved lemon, garlic, thyme, and rosemary.
Surround with chunked carrots. Roast 55-65 minutes until juices run clear.
Rest 10 minutes before carving.

title: Slow-Braised Short Ribs
description: Grass-fed beef short ribs braised low and slow with red wine and vegetables.
steps: Season ribs; sear in olive oil until deep brown on all sides.
Remove ribs; sauté diced onion, carrots, celery until soft.
Add tomato paste, wine, and broth; return ribs. Bring to simmer.
Cover and braise at 325°F for 2.5-3 hours until fork-tender.

title: Coconut Curry with Vegetables
description: Rich Thai-style curry with coconut milk, sweet potato, and spinach.
steps: Sauté ginger and garlic in coconut oil; add curry paste and stir 1 minute.
Add diced sweet potato and coconut milk; simmer 20-25 minutes.
Stir in spinach until wilted. Serve over rice or on its own.

title: Pan-Seared Duck Breast with Cherry Sauce
description: Crispy-skinned duck breast with a tart cherry and balsamic reduction.
steps: Score duck skin in a crosshatch pattern; season with salt.
Place skin-side down in a cold pan; cook over medium heat 12-15 min until crispy.
Flip and cook 4 minutes for medium-rare. Rest 5 minutes.
In the same pan, cook cherries and balsamic until syrupy. Spoon over sliced duck.

title: Whole Baked Trout with Lemon and Dill
description: Whole trout stuffed with lemon slices and fresh dill, baked until flaky.
steps: Preheat oven to 400°F. Rinse and pat trout dry.
Stuff cavities with lemon slices and dill. Drizzle with olive oil and salt.
Bake 20-25 minutes until flesh flakes easily.

title: Lamb Chops with Mint Chimichurri
description: Grilled lamb chops served with a vibrant fresh mint and parsley chimichurri.
steps: Season lamb chops with salt and pepper.
Grill 4-5 minutes per side for medium-rare.
Finely chop mint, parsley, and garlic; mix with vinegar and olive oil.
Spoon chimichurri over rested lamb chops.

title: Eggplant Parmesan (Grain-Free)
description: Breaded eggplant slices baked with marinara and melted mozzarella.
steps: Slice eggplant 0.5" thick; salt and let drain 10 minutes.
Dip in beaten egg, then almond flour. Bake at 400°F for 15 minutes.
Layer in dish: sauce, eggplant, mozzarella. Repeat.
Bake 15 minutes until bubbly; top with fresh basil.

title: Chicken and Sweet Potato Meal Prep Bowls
description: Roasted chicken breast and sweet potato with steamed broccoli — batch-ready.
steps: Preheat oven to 400°F. Cube sweet potatoes; dice chicken.
Toss with olive oil, garlic powder, paprika, salt, pepper.
Roast on sheet pans 20-25 minutes. Steam broccoli separately.
Divide into 6 containers for the week.

title: Beef and Vegetable Chili
description: Slow-cooked grass-fed beef chili loaded with beans and vegetables.
steps: Brown beef in a large pot; drain if needed.
Add diced onion, peppers, and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beans, spices, and 1 cup water.
Simmer 30-40 minutes. Stores well for 5 days.

title: Chicken Bone Broth
description: Nutrient-rich bone broth simmered for hours with vegetables and herbs.
steps: Place bones in a large pot; add vinegar and enough water to cover.
Add roughly chopped vegetables, bay leaves, and thyme.
Bring to a boil, reduce to a gentle simmer.
Cook 4-8 hours, skimming foam occasionally. Strain and store.

title: Turkey Bolognese Sauce
description: Rich, meaty bolognese made with ground turkey and San Marzano tomatoes.
steps: Finely dice carrot, celery, and onion (soffritto). Sauté in olive oil until soft.
Add turkey and brown, breaking into small pieces.
Add garlic, tomatoes, oregano, salt, pepper. Simmer 30-40 minutes.
Use over zucchini noodles, sweet potato, or spaghetti squash.

title: Coconut Lentil Dal
description: Creamy yellow lentils simmered in coconut milk with turmeric and garam masala.
steps: Sauté onion, garlic, and ginger until fragrant.
Add turmeric and garam masala; stir 30 seconds.
Add lentils and 3 cups water. Simmer 25 minutes until tender.
Stir in coconut milk; simmer 5 more minutes. Top with cilantro.

title: Pulled Pork (Slow Cooker)
description: Pork shoulder slow-cooked with apple cider vinegar and spices until shreddable.
steps: Rub pork with paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt.
Place in slow cooker; pour vinegar over.
Cook on low 8 hours until fall-apart tender.
Shred with forks; mix with pan juices. Stores 5-7 days.

title: Black Bean and Quinoa Freezer Burritos
description: Batch-made burritos with black beans, quinoa, and roasted vegetables in whole-wheat tortillas.
steps: Cook quinoa; drain and rinse beans.
Roast diced peppers and onion at 400°F for 15 minutes.
Mix beans, quinoa, roasted veg, and spices.
Fill tortillas, roll tightly, wrap in foil. Freeze for up to 3 months.

title: Egg Muffins (Weekly Batch)
description: Protein-packed egg cups with sausage, spinach, and cheese for grab-and-go breakfasts.
steps: Preheat oven to 375°F. Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Brown sausage; wilt spinach into it.
Distribute sausage mixture and cheese into cups.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; pour evenly. Bake 18-20 minutes.

title: Overnight Steel-Cut Oats (Big Batch)
description: A week's worth of steel-cut oats cooked in one pot, ready to reheat.
steps: Bring water to a boil; stir in oats, cinnamon, and salt.
Reduce heat and simmer 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in maple syrup. Divide into containers.
Reheat portions through the week with milk of choice and toppings.

title: Baked Salmon Cakes
description: Batch-baked salmon patties with herbs — great cold or reheated.
steps: Drain salmon; flake and mix with eggs, almond flour, green onions, mustard, lemon zest.
Form into 8 patties.
Bake at 400°F for 18-20 minutes, flipping halfway.
Cool and store in fridge up to 5 days.

title: Apple Slices with Almond Butter
description: Crisp apple slices paired with creamy almond butter.
steps: Core and slice apple.
Serve with almond butter for dipping.

title: Hard-Boiled Eggs
description: Simple hard-boiled eggs seasoned with sea salt and pepper.
steps: Boil eggs for 10-12 minutes.
Cool in ice water, peel, and season.

title: Trail Mix
description: Homemade trail mix with raw almonds, cashews, pumpkin seeds, and dried cranberries.
steps: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Shake to mix. Portion into bags.

title: Guacamole with Veggie Sticks
description: Fresh guacamole served with cucumber, carrot, and celery sticks.
steps: Mash avocados; stir in lime juice, diced tomato, onion, and minced jalapeño.
Cut cucumber and carrots into sticks.
Serve guacamole with veggie sticks.

title: Hummus with Cucumber Rounds
description: Homemade chickpea hummus topped with paprika, served with cucumber.
steps: Blend chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, olive oil, and salt until smooth.
Slice cucumbers into rounds.
Serve hummus with cucumber for dipping.

title: Energy Balls (Date and Coconut)
description: No-bake energy balls made with Medjool dates, coconut, and nuts.
steps: Blend dates and cashews in a food processor until sticky.
Add coconut, cacao, and vanilla; pulse to combine.
Roll into 12 balls; refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: Celery with Sunflower Seed Butter
description: Crunchy celery sticks spread with sunflower seed butter.
steps: Cut celery into sticks.
Spread or dip with sunflower seed butter.

title: Mixed Nuts and Dark Chocolate
description: A handful of mixed nuts paired with a square of 85%+ dark chocolate.
steps: Portion nuts and chocolate.
Enjoy as-is.

title: Frozen Banana Bites
description: Banana slices dipped in dark chocolate and frozen for a sweet treat.
steps: Slice bananas into rounds; place on parchment-lined tray.
Melt chocolate with coconut oil; dip each slice halfway.
Freeze 1-2 hours until solid.

title: Edamame with Sea Salt
description: Steamed edamame pods sprinkled with flaky sea salt.
steps: Boil or steam edamame for 4-5 minutes.
Drain and sprinkle with salt.

title: Salmon Poke Bowl
description: Sushi-grade salmon over rice with avocado, cucumber, and sesame.
steps: Cube salmon; toss with coconut aminos.
Slice avocado and cucumber.
Assemble bowls with rice, salmon, avocado, cucumber; top with sesame seeds.

title: Thai Chicken Lettuce Cups
description: Ground chicken with basil, lime, and chili in crisp lettuce cups.
steps: Sauté chicken in coconut oil until cooked through.
Add fish sauce, lime juice, and minced chili.
Toss in torn basil; spoon into lettuce cups.

title: Spaghetti Squash Carbonara
description: Roasted spaghetti squash with a creamy egg and parmesan sauce, topped with pancetta.
steps: Halve squash; roast cut-side down at 400°F for 35-40 minutes.
Crisp diced pancetta in a pan; add minced garlic.
Whisk eggs and parmesan together.
Scrape squash into strands; toss with pancetta, then egg mixture off heat. Season generously.

title: Grilled Steak with Chimichurri
description: Grass-fed ribeye steak with fresh herb chimichurri and grilled vegetables.
steps: Make chimichurri: finely chop parsley, oregano, garlic; mix with vinegar and oil.
Season steaks; grill 4-5 min per side for medium-rare.
Grill halved zucchini alongside.
Rest steaks 5 minutes; serve topped with chimichurri.

title: Thai Green Curry with Chicken
description: Aromatic green curry with chicken, bamboo shoots, and Thai basil.
steps: Heat coconut oil; fry curry paste 1 minute until fragrant.
Add chicken pieces; sear 3 minutes.
Pour in coconut milk, bamboo shoots, and fish sauce. Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in Thai basil. Serve over cauliflower rice or jasmine rice.

title: Mushroom Risotto (Cauliflower Base)
description: Creamy mushroom risotto using riced cauliflower instead of arborio rice.
steps: Rice cauliflower in food processor.
Sauté mushrooms in butter until golden; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic; add cauliflower rice and broth. Cook 5-7 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, parmesan, and thyme. Serve immediately.

title: Minestrone Soup
description: Italian vegetable soup with white beans, zucchini, and fresh herbs.
steps: Sauté diced onion, carrot, celery, and garlic in olive oil.
Add diced zucchini, tomatoes, broth, and beans.
Simmer 25-30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in fresh basil before serving. Freezes well.

title: Chicken Tikka Masala (Batch)
description: Tender chicken in a spiced tomato-coconut sauce. Make a big pot for the week.
steps: Cut chicken into chunks; season with garam masala, turmeric, and salt.
Sear chicken in coconut oil; set aside.
Sauté onion, garlic, ginger until golden.
Add tomatoes and coconut milk; return chicken. Simmer 25 minutes.

title: Roasted Vegetable and Quinoa Salad
description: Big-batch roasted veg and quinoa salad with lemon vinaigrette.
steps: Cook quinoa and let cool.
Dice vegetables; toss with olive oil. Roast at 425°F for 20-25 minutes.
Combine quinoa, roasted veg, lemon juice, and parsley.
Season well. Stores 5 days in the fridge.

title: Shepherd's Pie (Sweet Potato Topping)
description: Ground lamb and vegetable filling topped with mashed sweet potato.
steps: Boil sweet potatoes until tender; mash with salt.
Brown lamb with diced onion and carrot.
Add peas, tomato paste, and broth. Simmer 10 minutes.
Transfer to baking dish; spread sweet potato on top. Bake at 400°F for 20 minutes.

title: Baked Chicken Drumsticks (Batch)
description: Simple oven-baked drumsticks with garlic, paprika, and herbs.
steps: Preheat oven to 425°F.
Toss drumsticks with olive oil and seasonings.
Arrange on a baking sheet; bake 35-40 minutes until skin is crispy and internal temp is 165°F.
Let rest 5 minutes. Store extras for the week.

title: Stuffed Sweet Potatoes with Black Beans
description: Baked sweet potatoes stuffed with spiced black beans, salsa, and avocado.
steps: Bake sweet potatoes at 400°F for 40-45 minutes.
Warm beans with cumin.
Split potatoes; fill with beans, salsa, and sliced avocado.

title: Zucchini Noodles with Pesto
description: Spiralized zucchini tossed with fresh basil pesto and cherry tomatoes.
steps: Make pesto: blend basil, pine nuts, garlic, parmesan, and olive oil.
Spiralize zucchini; lightly warm in a pan 1-2 minutes.
Toss with pesto and halved cherry tomatoes.

title: Egg Drop Soup
description: Light, warming soup with whisked eggs in ginger-infused bone broth.
steps: Bring broth and ginger to a simmer.
Beat eggs; slowly pour into simmering broth in a thin stream, stirring gently.
Top with sliced green onions and a drizzle of sesame oil.

title: Coconut Chia Pudding
description: Thick chia pudding made with coconut milk, topped with mango.
steps: Mix chia seeds, coconut milk, maple syrup, and vanilla.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Top with diced mango before serving.

title: Baked Falafel Bowl
description: Oven-baked chickpea falafel over greens with tahini sauce.
steps: Pulse chickpeas, parsley, garlic, cumin, and almond flour in food processor.
Form into balls; bake at 400°F for 20 minutes, flipping halfway.
Serve over greens drizzled with tahini thinned with lemon juice.

title: Pan-Seared Tilapia with Mango Salsa
description: Lightly seasoned tilapia with a fresh mango and jalapeño salsa.
steps: Dice mango, onion, jalapeño; mix with lime juice and cilantro.
Season tilapia with salt and pepper; pan-sear in olive oil 3-4 min per side.
Top fish with mango salsa.

title: Roasted Brussels Sprouts with Bacon
description: Crispy roasted Brussels sprouts tossed with uncured bacon pieces.
steps: Halve Brussels sprouts; toss with olive oil, salt, pepper.
Chop bacon; scatter over sprouts on a baking sheet.
Roast at 400°F for 20-22 minutes. Drizzle with balsamic.

title: Butternut Squash Soup
description: Velvety roasted butternut squash soup with warming spices.
steps: Peel and cube squash; roast at 400°F for 25 minutes.
Sauté onion and garlic in coconut oil.
Add roasted squash and broth; blend until smooth.
Season with nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.

title: Asian Sesame Chicken Salad
description: Shredded chicken over cabbage with sesame-ginger dressing.
steps: Toss cabbage, carrot, and chicken.
Whisk sesame oil, coconut aminos, and ginger for dressing.
Drizzle and toss; top with sesame seeds.

title: Pork Chops with Apple and Sage
description: Pan-seared bone-in pork chops with caramelized apple and fresh sage.
steps: Season pork chops generously with salt and pepper.
Sear in olive oil 5-6 minutes per side until golden and cooked through.
In the same pan, cook sliced apple and sage until caramelized.
Serve apple and sage atop the pork chops with pan juices.

title: Veggie-Packed Frittata
description: A thick Italian egg bake loaded with seasonal vegetables and herbs.
steps: Preheat oven to 375°F. Sauté diced peppers and zucchini in olive oil.
Add spinach and wilt. Pour into a greased oven-safe skillet.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; pour over veg. Top with goat cheese.
Bake 22-25 minutes until set. Sprinkle with chives.

title: Taco Seasoned Ground Turkey Bowls
description: Taco-spiced turkey over cauliflower rice with toppings.
steps: Brown turkey; add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, and salt.
Warm cauliflower rice in a separate pan.
Divide into bowls; top with sliced avocado and salsa.

title: Banana Oat Muffins
description: Naturally sweetened muffins with banana, oats, and cinnamon.
steps: Blend bananas, oats, eggs, almond butter, cinnamon, and baking soda.
Pour into a greased 12-cup muffin tin.
Bake at 350°F for 18-20 minutes.

title: Cucumber Avocado Sushi Rolls (No Rice)
description: Fresh sushi rolls using thin cucumber sheets instead of rice.
steps: Use a mandoline to slice cucumbers into thin, wide strips.
Layer nori, cucumber strips, avocado slices, and salmon.
Roll tightly; slice into pieces. Serve with coconut aminos.

title: Bone Broth Ramen
description: Rich bone broth with zucchini noodles, soft-boiled egg, and scallions.
steps: Simmer broth with ginger and coconut aminos.
Soft-boil eggs (6.5 minutes); halve.
Add zucchini noodles to broth for 1 minute.
Serve topped with egg halves, scallions, and sesame oil.

title: Stuffed Portobello Mushrooms
description: Large portobello caps filled with ground beef, spinach, and mozzarella.
steps: Remove stems and scrape gills from mushrooms; brush with olive oil.
Brown beef with garlic; wilt spinach into it.
Fill caps with mixture; top with mozzarella.
Bake at 400°F for 15-18 minutes.

title: Watermelon and Feta Salad
description: Refreshing cubed watermelon with crumbled feta, mint, and lime.
steps: Cube watermelon; crumble feta.
Toss together with torn mint and lime juice.
Serve immediately.

title: Sweet Potato Toast with Almond Butter
description: Sliced sweet potato toasted and topped with almond butter and banana.
steps: Slice sweet potato lengthwise into 1/4 inch slabs.
Toast in a toaster on high 2-3 cycles until tender.
Top with almond butter, banana slices, and cinnamon.

title: Shakshuka
description: Eggs poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce.
steps: Sauté diced onion and pepper in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, cumin, paprika; simmer 5 minutes.
Make wells and crack eggs in; cover and cook 6-8 minutes.

title: Acai Bowl
description: Frozen acai blended thick and topped with granola, banana, and coconut.
steps: Blend acai, half the banana, and almond milk until thick.
Pour into bowl; top with sliced banana, granola, and coconut.

title: Smashed Chickpea Sandwich
description: Mashed chickpeas with celery and herbs on whole-grain bread.
steps: Drain chickpeas; mash roughly with a fork.
Mix with diced celery, onion, mustard, lemon juice, salt, pepper.
Spread on bread; serve as sandwiches.

title: Grilled Vegetable Platter
description: Seasonal vegetables grilled with olive oil and herbs.
steps: Slice vegetables into planks or wedges.
Toss with olive oil, thyme, salt, pepper.
Grill 4-5 minutes per side until charred and tender.

title: Chicken Salad with Grapes and Pecans
description: Shredded chicken mixed with halved grapes, pecans, and a yogurt dressing.
steps: Combine chicken, grapes, pecans, and celery.
Fold in yogurt; season with salt and pepper.
Serve in lettuce cups or over greens.

title: Beef Stew with Root Vegetables
description: Hearty beef stew slow-simmered with potatoes, carrots, and celery.
steps: Brown beef in batches in olive oil; set aside.
Sauté onion, celery; add tomato paste.
Return beef; add broth, diced potatoes, carrots.
Simmer covered 90 minutes until tender.

title: Coconut Shrimp (Baked)
description: Crunchy baked shrimp coated in shredded coconut.
steps: Set up dredging: almond flour, beaten eggs, shredded coconut.
Coat each shrimp through all three.
Bake on a lined sheet at 400°F for 10-12 minutes.

title: Sardines on Sourdough
description: Wild-caught sardines on toast with lemon, red onion, and arugula.
steps: Toast sourdough.
Top with arugula, sardines, red onion.
Squeeze lemon over and season with salt.

title: Bison Burgers
description: Lean bison patties with caramelized onions in a lettuce wrap.
steps: Form bison into 4 patties; season well.
Grill 4 min per side.
Caramelize sliced onion in olive oil.
Serve in lettuce wraps with avocado.

title: Chicken Congee
description: Comforting rice porridge with shredded chicken, ginger, and scallions.
steps: Bring broth, rice, ginger slices, and chicken to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 50-60 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken; shred and return to pot.
Serve topped with scallions and sesame oil.

title: Roasted Chickpeas (Snack)
description: Crunchy oven-roasted chickpeas seasoned with smoked paprika.
steps: Drain and dry chickpeas thoroughly.
Toss with oil and spices.
Roast at 400°F for 25-30 min, shaking halfway.

title: Mashed Cauliflower
description: Creamy mashed cauliflower with garlic and butter — low-carb side dish.
steps: Steam cauliflower florets until very tender (12-15 min).
Blend with butter, roasted garlic, and salt until smooth.
Adjust seasoning and serve.

title: Kimchi Fried Cauliflower Rice
description: Spicy kimchi stir-fried with riced cauliflower, egg, and scallions.
steps: Heat sesame oil; scramble eggs and set aside.
Stir-fry cauliflower rice 3 min; add chopped kimchi.
Add coconut aminos and egg; toss with scallions.

title: Cabbage Roll Soup
description: Unstuffed cabbage roll soup with ground pork, tomato, and herbs.
steps: Brown pork with onion and garlic.
Add shredded cabbage, tomatoes, broth, and thyme.
Simmer 25-30 minutes until cabbage is tender.

title: Sweet Potato Black Bean Chili
description: Vegetarian chili with sweet potato, black beans, and warming spices.
steps: Sauté diced onion and garlic.
Add cubed sweet potato, spices, tomatoes, beans, and 1 cup water.
Simmer 25-30 minutes until sweet potato is tender.

title: Pan-Fried Sole with Lemon Butter
description: Delicate sole fillets pan-fried in butter with lemon and capers.
steps: Season sole with salt and pepper.
Pan-fry in butter 2-3 minutes per side.
Add lemon juice and capers to pan; spoon over fish.

title: Turkey and Zucchini Meatloaf
description: Moist meatloaf made with shredded zucchini and ground turkey.
steps: Mix turkey, grated zucchini, eggs, almond flour, garlic, and oregano.
Press into a loaf pan; brush top with tomato paste.
Bake at 375°F for 45-50 minutes.
Rest 10 minutes before slicing.

title: Kale and White Bean Soup
description: Italian-style soup with lacinato kale, white beans, and garlic.
steps: Sauté onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add broth and beans; simmer 15 min.
Add chopped kale; cook 5-8 minutes until tender.
Finish with lemon juice and olive oil drizzle.

title: Chicken Shawarma Bowl
description: Spiced chicken with pickled onion, hummus, and fresh vegetables.
steps: Season chicken with cumin, turmeric, paprika, salt.
Sear in olive oil 5-6 min per side; rest and slice.
Assemble bowls with chicken, diced cucumber, tomatoes, hummus.

title: Broiled Grapefruit
description: Warm broiled grapefruit halves with cinnamon and a touch of honey.
steps: Halve grapefruits; loosen segments with a knife.
Drizzle with honey and sprinkle cinnamon.
Broil 4-5 minutes until bubbling and lightly caramelized.

title: Beef Liver Pâté
description: Nutrient-dense pâté made with grass-fed liver, butter, and herbs.
steps: Sauté onion and garlic in 1 tbsp butter.
Add liver; cook 4-5 min per side until just pink inside.
Blend liver, onion, remaining butter, and thyme until smooth.
Pour into ramekins; chill at least 2 hours.

title: Cauliflower Steaks with Chimichurri
description: Thick-cut cauliflower steaks roasted and topped with fresh chimichurri.
steps: Slice cauliflower into 1-inch steaks.
Brush with olive oil; roast at 425°F for 20-25 minutes.
Make chimichurri: chop parsley, garlic; mix with vinegar, oil, pepper flakes.
Spoon chimichurri over roasted steaks.

title: Lamb Kofta with Tzatziki
description: Spiced lamb meatballs served with cooling cucumber yogurt sauce.
steps: Mix lamb with cumin, coriander, parsley, salt, pepper. Form into small ovals.
Grill or broil 5-6 min per side.
Make tzatziki: mix yogurt, grated cucumber, minced garlic, salt.
Serve kofta with tzatziki.

title: Roasted Beet Hummus
description: Vibrant pink hummus made with roasted beets and tahini.
steps: Blend beets, chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, and olive oil.
Add water 1 tbsp at a time until desired consistency.
Season with salt. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: Stuffed Dates with Goat Cheese and Walnuts
description: Medjool dates stuffed with tangy goat cheese and topped with walnut.
steps: Pit dates and open slightly.
Fill each with a small amount of goat cheese.
Press a walnut half on top.

title: Curried Egg Salad
description: Hard-boiled eggs mashed with curry powder, yogurt, and fresh herbs.
steps: Chop eggs roughly; mix with yogurt and curry powder.
Add celery and cilantro; season with salt.
Serve in lettuce cups or on toast.

title: Pesto Chicken Meal Prep
description: Batch-cooked chicken breast with basil pesto and roasted cherry tomatoes.
steps: Make pesto: blend basil, pine nuts, parmesan, and olive oil.
Spread pesto over chicken breasts.
Surround with cherry tomatoes on a sheet pan.
Bake at 400°F for 20-22 minutes. Divide into containers.

title: Miso Soup with Tofu
description: Traditional miso soup with silken tofu, wakame, and scallions.
steps: Bring water to a gentle simmer (do not boil hard).
Rehydrate wakame in the water for 2 minutes.
Dissolve miso paste into the broth. Add cubed tofu.
Serve topped with sliced scallions.

title: Spiced Sweet Potato Fries
description: Oven-baked sweet potato fries with cumin and smoked paprika.
steps: Cut sweet potatoes into thin fries.
Toss with olive oil and spices.
Bake at 425°F for 22-25 min, flipping halfway.

title: Salmon Avocado Bowl
description: Baked salmon flaked over greens with avocado, radish, and lemon.
steps: Bake salmon at 400°F for 10-12 minutes.
Arrange greens in bowls; top with flaked salmon, avocado, sliced radishes.
Drizzle with lemon juice and olive oil.

title: Almond Crusted Chicken Tenders
description: Chicken tenders coated in almond flour and baked until crispy.
steps: Mix almond flour with garlic powder, paprika, and salt.
Dip tenders in beaten egg, then coat in almond flour mixture.
Bake at 400°F for 16-18 minutes, flipping halfway.

title: Mediterranean Stuffed Tomatoes
description: Large tomatoes stuffed with quinoa, olives, feta, and herbs.
steps: Hollow out tomatoes, keeping shells intact.
Mix quinoa with olives, crumbled feta, basil.
Fill tomatoes; drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 375°F for 18-20 minutes.

title: Teriyaki Salmon Bowls (Batch)
description: Baked salmon glazed with homemade teriyaki over rice with steamed veg.
steps: Mix coconut aminos, honey, ginger, minced garlic.
Place salmon on a sheet pan; pour glaze over.
Bake at 400°F for 15-18 minutes.
Divide with rice and steamed broccoli into containers.

title: Breakfast Sausage Patties
description: Homemade pork sausage patties seasoned with sage and garlic.
steps: Mix pork with sage, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Form into 8 patties.
Cook in a skillet 4-5 minutes per side.

title: Grilled Peach and Arugula Salad
description: Grilled peach halves over arugula with prosciutto and balsamic.
steps: Halve and pit peaches; grill cut-side down 3-4 minutes.
Arrange arugula on plates with prosciutto.
Top with grilled peaches; drizzle with balsamic and olive oil.

title: Coconut Chicken Strips
description: Chicken tenders coated in shredded coconut, baked until golden.
steps: Dip chicken in beaten eggs, then press into coconut mixed with garlic powder and salt.
Arrange on parchment-lined sheet.
Bake at 400°F for 16-18 minutes.

title: Loaded Baked Potato
description: Russet potato baked and topped with grass-fed butter, chives, and sour cream.
steps: Prick potatoes with a fork; bake at 400°F for 45-50 min.
Split open; add butter, sour cream, and chives.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: Veggie Fritters
description: Crispy pan-fried fritters with grated carrot, zucchini, and herbs.
steps: Squeeze moisture from grated vegetables.
Mix with eggs, almond flour, dill, salt, and pepper.
Pan-fry in olive oil, 3-4 minutes per side until golden.

title: Moroccan Chicken with Apricots
description: Braised chicken thighs with dried apricots, olives, and warm spices.
steps: Brown chicken in olive oil; set aside.
Sauté sliced onion with cumin and cinnamon.
Add broth, apricots, olives; return chicken.
Cover and braise 30-35 minutes until tender.

title: Soba Noodle Bowl (Buckwheat)
description: 100% buckwheat noodles with edamame, cucumber, and sesame dressing.
steps: Cook soba noodles per package; rinse with cold water.
Toss with edamame, sliced cucumber, sesame oil, and coconut aminos.
Top with sesame seeds.

title: Chocolate Avocado Mousse
description: Rich, dairy-free mousse made with avocado, cacao, and maple syrup.
steps: Blend all ingredients until silky smooth.
Chill 30 minutes for best texture.
Serve in small cups.

title: Lamb Burgers with Feta
description: Ground lamb patties with crumbled feta and fresh mint.
steps: Mix lamb with feta and mint; form 4 patties.
Grill 4-5 minutes per side.
Serve in lettuce wraps with tomato slices.

title: Roasted Red Pepper Soup
description: Silky roasted red pepper soup with basil and a drizzle of olive oil.
steps: Roast halved peppers at 425°F for 20 minutes until charred.
Sauté onion and garlic.
Blend peppers, onion, garlic, and broth until smooth.
Season and garnish with basil and olive oil.

title: Wild Rice and Mushroom Pilaf
description: Earthy wild rice cooked with mushrooms, thyme, and bone broth.
steps: Sauté mushrooms and onion in olive oil until golden.
Add rice, broth, and thyme. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover, and simmer 40-45 minutes.
Fluff with a fork; discard thyme sprigs.

title: Ceviche
description: Fresh white fish marinated in lime juice with onion, cilantro, and avocado.
steps: Cut fish into small cubes; toss with lime juice.
Refrigerate 30-60 minutes until opaque.
Fold in onion, cilantro, jalapeño, and diced avocado.
Season with salt; serve with plantain chips.

title: Sun-Dried Tomato and Olive Chicken
description: Chicken breast baked with sun-dried tomatoes, olives, and capers.
steps: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Top with sun-dried tomatoes, olives, and capers.
Drizzle with olive oil; sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 400°F for 20-22 minutes.

title: Tahini Date Shake
description: Creamy shake with Medjool dates, tahini, banana, and almond milk.
steps: Add all ingredients to a blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Pour and drink immediately.

title: Herb-Roasted Cornish Hen
description: Individual Cornish game hens roasted with garlic, herbs, and lemon.
steps: Preheat oven to 425°F. Pat hens dry.
Stuff cavities with garlic, rosemary, and lemon quarters.
Rub with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Roast 45-50 minutes until golden and juices run clear.

title: Spicy Tuna Stuffed Avocado
description: Avocado halves filled with spiced tuna, lime, and sriracha.
steps: Drain tuna; mix with lime juice and sriracha.
Halve avocados and remove pits.
Fill each half with spicy tuna; sprinkle sesame seeds.

title: Roasted Cauliflower Tacos
description: Spiced roasted cauliflower in corn tortillas with cabbage slaw.
steps: Toss cauliflower florets with olive oil, chili, cumin, salt.
Roast at 425°F for 18-20 minutes.
Make slaw with cabbage and lime juice.
Assemble tacos with cauliflower and slaw.

title: Coconut Macaroons
description: Simple three-ingredient coconut macaroons made with egg whites and honey.
steps: Whisk egg whites until frothy; mix in honey and vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Scoop onto parchment; bake at 325°F for 15-18 minutes.

title: Italian Wedding Soup
description: Light broth soup with turkey meatballs, escarole, and carrots.
steps: Mix turkey, egg, almond flour, minced garlic, salt. Form tiny meatballs.
Bring broth to a simmer; add carrots.
Drop in meatballs; cook 10 minutes.
Add escarole; simmer 5 more minutes.

title: Pan-Seared Scallops with Brown Butter
description: Perfectly seared sea scallops in nutty brown butter with lemon.
steps: Pat scallops very dry; season with salt.
Heat butter until foaming; sear scallops 2 min per side.
Add thyme to the brown butter; spoon over scallops.
Squeeze lemon over and serve immediately.

title: Carrot Ginger Soup
description: Bright, smooth carrot soup with fresh ginger and a hint of coconut milk.
steps: Sauté onion and ginger in coconut oil.
Add chopped carrots and broth; simmer 20 minutes.
Blend until smooth; stir in coconut milk.
Season with salt and serve.

title: Crispy Baked Chicken Wings
description: Simple oven-baked wings seasoned with garlic and black pepper.
steps: Pat wings dry. Toss with baking powder and seasonings.
Arrange on a wire rack over a baking sheet.
Bake at 425°F for 35-40 minutes, flipping at 20 min.
Serve with your favorite whole-food dipping sauce.

title: Smoked Mackerel Salad
description: Flaked smoked mackerel over mixed greens with pickled onion and horseradish.
steps: Flake mackerel into chunks.
Toss greens with olive oil and lemon juice.
Top with mackerel and thinly sliced red onion.
Add a small dollop of horseradish.

title: Sweet Potato Brownies
description: Fudgy brownies made with sweet potato, cacao, and almond butter.
steps: Blend cooked sweet potato, almond butter, cacao, maple syrup, and vanilla.
Pour into a lined 8x8 pan.
Bake at 350°F for 20-25 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: Poached Pears with Cinnamon
description: Whole pears gently poached in spiced water with cinnamon and star anise.
steps: Peel pears, leaving stems intact.
Simmer in water with cinnamon, star anise, and honey 20-25 min.
Serve warm with a spoonful of poaching liquid.

title: Balsamic Glazed Pork Tenderloin
description: Roasted pork tenderloin with a sweet balsamic and garlic glaze.
steps: Sear tenderloin in olive oil on all sides.
Whisk balsamic, honey, and garlic; pour over pork.
Add rosemary; roast at 400°F for 20-25 minutes.
Rest 5 minutes; slice and spoon pan sauce over.

title: Fried Plantains
description: Sweet ripe plantains pan-fried in coconut oil until caramelized.
steps: Peel plantains; slice on a diagonal.
Fry in coconut oil 2-3 minutes per side until golden.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: Greek Lamb Stew
description: Slow-cooked lamb with potatoes, tomatoes, and oregano.
steps: Brown lamb in olive oil in batches.
Sauté onion and garlic; add tomatoes, broth, oregano.
Return lamb; add cubed potatoes.
Simmer covered 90 minutes until tender.

title: Fresh Spring Rolls (Rice Paper)
description: Rice paper rolls filled with shrimp, vermicelli, and fresh herbs.
steps: Cook vermicelli per package; cool.
Dip rice paper in warm water until pliable.
Layer lettuce, noodles, herbs, shrimp in center; fold sides and roll.
Serve with coconut aminos for dipping.

title: Turmeric Golden Milk
description: Warm, spiced milk drink with turmeric, ginger, and cinnamon.
steps: Heat coconut milk with turmeric, ginger, and cinnamon.
Whisk until frothy and warm.
Sweeten with honey; drink warm.

title: Baked Eggs in Avocado
description: Eggs baked directly inside avocado halves with salt and hot sauce.
steps: Halve avocados; scoop out a bit extra to fit egg.
Crack an egg into each half; season.
Bake at 400°F for 12-15 minutes until egg is set.

title: Beef and Broccoli Stir-Fry
description: Thinly sliced grass-fed beef stir-fried with broccoli in a ginger-garlic sauce.
steps: Slice steak thin against the grain.
Stir-fry in coconut oil 3 minutes; set aside.
Add broccoli and 2 tbsp water; cover 3 minutes.
Return beef; add coconut aminos, ginger, garlic. Toss 1 minute.

title: Mixed Berry Crumble
description: Warm mixed berries topped with an oat-almond crumble, naturally sweetened.
steps: Spread berries in a baking dish.
Mix oats, almond flour, coconut oil, maple syrup, and cinnamon.
Crumble topping over berries.
Bake at 375°F for 22-25 minutes until golden and bubbly.

title: Chicken Biryani
description: Fragrant basmati rice layered with spiced chicken, saffron, and crispy onions.
steps: Marinate chicken in yogurt, garam masala, turmeric, ginger, garlic for 1 hour.
Fry sliced onions in ghee until deep golden; set half aside for garnish.
Sear marinated chicken with remaining onions; cook 10 minutes.
Par-cook rice with whole spices; layer over chicken with saffron milk.
Seal pot and cook on low heat 25 minutes. Garnish with fried onions, cilantro, mint.

title: Chana Masala
description: Chickpeas simmered in a robust tomato-onion gravy with warm spices.
steps: Sauté onion in ghee until golden; add garlic, ginger, and all spices.
Add crushed tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes until thick.
Add drained chickpeas; simmer 15 minutes. Mash a few for creaminess.
Finish with lemon juice and cilantro.

title: Palak Paneer
description: Cubes of paneer in a velvety spiced spinach sauce.
steps: Blanch spinach 2 minutes; blend into a smooth puree.
Sauté onion, garlic, ginger in ghee; add cumin and garam masala.
Add spinach puree; simmer 5 minutes.
Pan-fry paneer cubes until golden; fold into spinach sauce.

title: Lamb Rogan Josh
description: Kashmiri-style braised lamb in a rich, aromatic red sauce.
steps: Brown lamb in batches in ghee; set aside.
Sauté onions until deep golden; add ginger, garlic, all spices.
Add yogurt 1 tbsp at a time, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and lamb; cover and braise 90 minutes until fork-tender.

title: Dal Tadka
description: Yellow lentils tempered with cumin, garlic, and dried chilies in ghee.
steps: Boil lentils with turmeric and salt until very soft, about 20 minutes.
In a small pan, heat ghee; add cumin, garlic, and dried chilies until sizzling.
Add diced tomato to the tadka; cook 1 minute.
Pour sizzling tadka over the dal. Garnish with cilantro.

title: Aloo Gobi
description: Dry-roasted cauliflower and potatoes with turmeric, cumin, and ginger.
steps: Cut cauliflower into florets; dice potatoes into small cubes.
Heat coconut oil; sauté onion, ginger until softened.
Add turmeric, cumin, coriander; toss in potatoes. Cook covered 10 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cook uncovered 10 minutes until tender and golden. Top with cilantro.

title: Butter Chicken (Murgh Makhani)
description: Tender chicken in a rich, creamy tomato-butter sauce with warm spices.
steps: Marinate chicken in yogurt, garam masala, and turmeric for 30 minutes.
Grill or broil chicken until charred; cut into pieces.
Sauté garlic and ginger in butter; add tomatoes and simmer 15 min.
Blend sauce smooth; add coconut milk, honey, chicken. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: Keema Matar
description: Spiced ground lamb with green peas in a fragrant tomato-onion base.
steps: Sauté onion in ghee; add garlic, ginger, and spices.
Add ground lamb; brown well, breaking into small pieces.
Add tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes. Add peas and cook 5 more minutes.

title: Pad Thai (Rice Noodles)
description: Stir-fried rice noodles with shrimp, egg, bean sprouts, and tamarind sauce.
steps: Soak rice noodles in hot water 8 minutes; drain.
Stir-fry shrimp in coconut oil 2 min; push aside, scramble eggs.
Add noodles, tamarind, fish sauce; toss until coated.
Add bean sprouts; serve with lime, peanuts, and green onions.

title: Tom Yum Soup
description: Hot and sour Thai soup with shrimp, lemongrass, galangal, and lime leaves.
steps: Simmer 4 cups water with bruised lemongrass, ginger, and chilies 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes; cook 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and fish sauce; cook 3 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat; add lime juice and cilantro.

title: Massaman Curry
description: Rich, mild Thai curry with beef, potatoes, peanuts, and coconut milk.
steps: Fry curry paste in coconut oil 1 minute.
Add beef; sear until browned. Pour in coconut milk.
Add potatoes, onion, cinnamon, cardamom, fish sauce, and tamarind.
Simmer 50-60 minutes until beef is tender. Top with peanuts.

title: Larb Gai (Thai Chicken Salad)
description: Minced chicken tossed with toasted rice powder, herbs, lime, and chilies.
steps: Cook chicken in a dry pan, breaking it up finely.
Off heat, toss with lime juice, fish sauce, chilies, onion.
Add herbs and toasted rice powder; mix well.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: Tom Kha Gai
description: Coconut milk soup with chicken, galangal, lemongrass, and lime.
steps: Simmer 2 cups broth with lemongrass and ginger 5 minutes.
Add chicken and mushrooms; cook 10 minutes.
Pour in coconut milk and fish sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add lime juice. Garnish with cilantro.

title: Bibimbap
description: Rice bowl topped with sautéed vegetables, beef, fried egg, and gochujang.
steps: Cook rice. Slice steak thin; marinate in coconut aminos and sesame oil.
Sauté each vegetable separately with a pinch of salt and sesame oil.
Sear steak 1-2 minutes per side. Fry eggs sunny-side up.
Assemble bowls: rice, veggies, steak, egg, gochujang, sesame seeds.

title: Kimchi Jjigae (Kimchi Stew)
description: Fermented kimchi stew with pork belly, tofu, and scallions.
steps: Sauté pork in sesame oil until browned.
Add kimchi and garlic; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add 3 cups water, gochugaru, and fish sauce. Bring to boil.
Slide in tofu; simmer 15 minutes. Top with scallions.

title: Bulgogi (Korean BBQ Beef)
description: Thinly sliced beef marinated in a sweet soy-pear marinade, grilled or pan-seared.
steps: Freeze steak 20 min for easy slicing; cut paper-thin against the grain.
Mix coconut aminos, sesame oil, garlic, ginger, grated pear. Marinate 30 min.
Sear on high heat 2-3 minutes per batch — don't crowd the pan.
Garnish with scallions and sesame seeds.

title: Japchae (Glass Noodle Stir-Fry)
description: Sweet potato noodles stir-fried with vegetables, beef, and sesame.
steps: Cook noodles per package; drain and toss with 1 tbsp sesame oil.
Sauté each vegetable and beef separately; season with coconut aminos.
Combine everything in a large bowl; toss well.
Garnish with sesame seeds. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: Korean Short Ribs (Galbi)
description: Grilled beef short ribs marinated in a sweet and savory Korean sauce.
steps: Mix coconut aminos, sesame oil, garlic, ginger, grated pear.
Marinate ribs at least 2 hours (overnight is best).
Grill on high heat 4-5 minutes per side.
Garnish with scallions and sesame seeds.

title: Carnitas
description: Slow-cooked pork shoulder braised in citrus and spices until fall-apart tender.
steps: Rub pork with cumin, oregano, and salt.
Place in slow cooker with garlic, orange and lime juice.
Cook on low 8 hours until shreddable.
Shred pork; broil 5 minutes to crisp the edges.

title: Pozole Rojo
description: Hearty Mexican hominy soup with pork in a rich red chili broth.
steps: Simmer pork in salted water 60 minutes; skim foam.
Toast and rehydrate guajillo chilies; blend with garlic into a smooth paste.
Add chili paste, hominy, oregano, cumin to the pork broth. Simmer 30 min.
Serve topped with radishes, lime, cilantro, shredded cabbage.

title: Chicken Mole Negro
description: Chicken braised in a complex, dark mole sauce with chili, chocolate, and spices.
steps: Toast and rehydrate dried chilies. Toast sesame seeds and almonds.
Blend chilies, onion, garlic, sesame, almonds, cumin, cinnamon, broth until smooth.
Simmer sauce 20 minutes; add chocolate until melted.
Add chicken; braise covered 40-45 minutes until cooked through.

title: Carne Asada
description: Charred, marinated flank steak with chimichurri, lime, and grilled onions.
steps: Marinate steak in lime, garlic, cumin, cilantro, jalapeño, olive oil for 1 hour.
Grill on high 4-5 minutes per side for medium.
Rest 5 minutes; slice thin against the grain.
Serve with grilled onions, salsa, and warm tortillas.

title: Doro Wot (Ethiopian Chicken Stew)
description: Slow-cooked chicken in a deeply spiced berbere-onion sauce with hard-boiled eggs.
steps: Dry-sauté onions (no oil) 15-20 minutes until deeply caramelized and jammy.
Add ghee, garlic, ginger, and berbere; cook 5 minutes.
Nestle chicken pieces into the sauce; add 0.5 cup water.
Cover and simmer 45-60 minutes. Score eggs; nestle into stew last 10 minutes.

title: Misir Wot (Ethiopian Red Lentil Stew)
description: Warmly spiced red lentils in a berbere-tomato sauce.
steps: Sauté onions in olive oil until soft; add garlic and berbere.
Add tomato paste; cook 2 minutes.
Add lentils and 3 cups water. Simmer 25-30 minutes until tender.
Season with salt. Serve with injera or rice.

title: Tibs (Ethiopian Sautéed Beef)
description: Cubed beef sautéed with onions, jalapeños, rosemary, and tomatoes.
steps: Heat ghee on high; sear beef cubes until browned all over.
Add onion and jalapeño; cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic, rosemary. Cook 3-4 more minutes.
Season with salt and serve immediately.

title: Chicken Shawarma Plate
description: Warm-spiced, yogurt-marinated chicken served with pickles, tahini, and salad.
steps: Marinate chicken in yogurt, cumin, turmeric, paprika, cinnamon, garlic for 1 hour.
Grill or pan-sear 6-7 minutes per side until charred and cooked.
Make tahini sauce: thin tahini with lemon juice and water.
Serve sliced chicken with chopped salad, pickles, and tahini drizzle.

title: Mujaddara (Lentils and Rice)
description: Earthy lentils and rice topped with deeply caramelized onions.
steps: Fry onions in olive oil 20-25 minutes until deeply caramelized; set aside.
Cook lentils in water 15 minutes until almost done.
Add rice and cumin; cook covered 15 more minutes.
Fluff and top with caramelized onions. Serve with yogurt.

title: Kofta Kebab
description: Grilled spiced lamb kebabs with parsley, onion, and warm spices.
steps: Mix lamb with onion, parsley, and all spices.
Form into elongated kebabs around skewers.
Grill 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through.
Serve with tahini, pickled turnips, and flatbread.

title: Maqluba (Upside-Down Rice)
description: Layered rice, eggplant, and spiced chicken flipped upside down to serve.
steps: Fry eggplant slices until golden; drain on paper towels.
Brown chicken with turmeric, cinnamon, cardamom.
Layer in pot: eggplant, chicken, soaked rice. Add broth to cover.
Cook covered 30-40 minutes. Flip onto a platter; garnish with pine nuts.

title: Fattoush
description: Crunchy Lebanese bread salad with sumac, pomegranate, and fresh herbs.
steps: Toast pita pieces until crisp.
Chop all vegetables; toss with herbs.
Whisk olive oil, lemon juice, and sumac for dressing.
Toss everything together; top with pomegranate seeds. Serve immediately.

title: Jollof Rice
description: West African one-pot rice simmered in a rich tomato-pepper sauce.
steps: Blend tomatoes, peppers, onion, garlic, ginger into a smooth puree.
Heat coconut oil; fry tomato paste 2 minutes. Add puree and cook 15 min.
Add rice, broth, scotch bonnet (whole), bay leaves, thyme.
Cover tightly and cook on lowest heat 25-30 min. Do not stir. Fluff and serve.

title: Groundnut Stew (Maafe)
description: West African peanut stew with chicken, sweet potato, and tomatoes.
steps: Brown chicken in coconut oil; set aside.
Sauté onion, garlic, ginger until soft.
Add tomatoes, peanut butter, 2 cups water; stir until smooth.
Return chicken; add sweet potato and scotch bonnet. Simmer 35-40 minutes.

title: Suya Skewers
description: Nigerian-style spiced beef skewers with a peanut-chili rub.
steps: Mix ground peanuts with paprika, cayenne, onion powder, garlic powder, ginger, salt.
Slice beef thin; thread onto skewers. Coat generously with suya spice.
Grill on high 3-4 minutes per side.
Serve with sliced onions and tomatoes.

title: Jerk Chicken
description: Scotch bonnet and allspice marinated chicken, grilled until smoky and charred.
steps: Blend scotch bonnet, scallions, garlic, thyme, allspice, coconut aminos, lime, cinnamon, nutmeg.
Score chicken deeply; coat with marinade. Refrigerate 4-24 hours.
Grill on medium heat 25-30 minutes, turning occasionally.
Rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: Curry Goat
description: Jamaican-style goat meat slow-braised in a rich curry sauce with potatoes.
steps: Season goat with curry powder, garlic, thyme, salt, pepper. Marinate 2 hours.
Brown goat in coconut oil in batches.
Add onion, scotch bonnet, 3 cups water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1.5-2 hours. Add potatoes last 30 minutes.

title: Oxtail Stew (Caribbean)
description: Slow-braised oxtail in a thick, savory gravy with butter beans.
steps: Season oxtail with allspice, salt, pepper. Brown in batches.
Sauté onion, garlic, carrots. Add tomato paste and coconut aminos.
Return oxtail; add thyme and 4 cups water. Bring to boil.
Simmer covered 2.5-3 hours until fall-off-the-bone. Add beans last 30 min.

title: Miso Glazed Salmon
description: Salmon marinated in white miso, mirin, and ginger, then broiled until caramelized.
steps: Mix miso, mirin, ginger, and sesame oil into a paste.
Coat salmon fillets; marinate 30 minutes (or overnight).
Broil 8-10 minutes until glaze is caramelized and fish flakes.
Garnish with sliced green onions.

title: Gyudon (Beef Bowl)
description: Thinly sliced beef simmered in a sweet-savory broth over steamed rice.
steps: Simmer onion in coconut aminos, mirin, ginger, and 0.5 cup water for 5 min.
Add beef slices; cook 5-8 minutes until tender.
Serve over rice. Top with a soft-boiled or raw egg yolk and scallions.

title: Chicken Katsu (Almond Flour)
description: Crispy almond-flour-breaded chicken cutlet with tonkatsu sauce.
steps: Pound chicken to even thickness. Season with salt.
Dip in beaten egg, then press into almond flour.
Pan-fry in coconut oil 5-6 minutes per side until golden.
Slice; serve with shredded cabbage and tonkatsu sauce (coconut aminos + tomato paste).

title: Kung Pao Chicken
description: Spicy stir-fried chicken with peanuts, dried chilies, and Sichuan peppercorns.
steps: Toss chicken with 1 tbsp coconut aminos. Stir-fry in coconut oil 5 min; set aside.
Fry dried chilies and peanuts in sesame oil 30 seconds.
Add garlic, ginger; stir 30 sec. Return chicken.
Add remaining coconut aminos, vinegar, scallions. Toss and serve.

title: Mapo Tofu
description: Silky tofu in a fiery, numbing chili-bean sauce with ground pork.
steps: Brown pork in coconut oil; add garlic, ginger, and doubanjiang.
Add 1 cup water or broth; bring to simmer.
Gently slide in cubed tofu; simmer 8 minutes.
Finish with Sichuan pepper, sesame oil, and scallions.

title: Char Siu Pork
description: Cantonese-style barbecue pork with a sweet, sticky glaze.
steps: Mix coconut aminos, honey, five spice, garlic, sesame oil, tomato paste.
Marinate pork 4 hours or overnight.
Roast at 425°F for 30-35 minutes, basting every 10 min.
Rest 5 min; slice thin.

title: Pho Bo (Beef Pho)
description: Aromatic beef broth with rice noodles, rare sliced beef, and fresh herbs.
steps: Simmer broth with charred ginger, onion, star anise, cinnamon 45 minutes.
Strain; add fish sauce. Keep at a rolling simmer.
Cook rice noodles separately; divide into bowls.
Lay raw steak over hot noodles; pour boiling broth over (cooks the beef). Serve with herbs, sprouts, lime.

title: Bun Cha (Hanoi Grilled Pork)
description: Chargrilled pork patties and belly with rice vermicelli, herbs, and dipping sauce.
steps: Mix pork with garlic, 1 tbsp fish sauce, honey. Form into small patties.
Grill 4-5 minutes per side until charred.
Cook vermicelli; drain. Make dipping sauce: fish sauce, lime, chili, water.
Serve patties with noodles, lettuce, herbs, and dipping sauce.

title: Lemongrass Chicken (Ga Xao Sa Ot)
description: Stir-fried chicken with lemongrass, chili, and garlic — intensely fragrant.
steps: Toss chicken with fish sauce and coconut aminos.
Stir-fry lemongrass, garlic, chili in coconut oil 1 minute.
Add chicken; cook on high 8-10 minutes until golden and fragrant.
Toss with scallions and serve over rice.

title: Lamb Tagine with Apricots and Almonds
description: Slow-braised lamb with dried apricots, almonds, and Moroccan spices.
steps: Brown lamb in olive oil; set aside.
Sauté onion, garlic, ginger with cumin, turmeric, cinnamon.
Return lamb; add 1.5 cups water, apricots, honey. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 90 minutes. Toast almonds; garnish with almonds and cilantro.

title: Harira (Moroccan Tomato Lentil Soup)
description: Hearty Moroccan soup with lentils, chickpeas, tomatoes, and warming spices.
steps: Sauté onion, celery, garlic, ginger in olive oil.
Add cumin, cinnamon, turmeric; stir 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes, lentils, chickpeas, and 4 cups water. Simmer 30-35 minutes.
Finish with lemon juice and fresh cilantro.

title: Nasi Goreng (Indonesian Fried Rice)
description: Smoky, savory fried rice with shrimp paste, egg, and sweet soy.
steps: Stir-fry garlic and chili in coconut oil 30 seconds.
Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes. Push aside; scramble eggs.
Add rice; toss on high heat 3-4 minutes. Add coconut aminos.
Garnish with scallions; serve with lime wedges.

title: Beef Rendang
description: Slow-cooked Indonesian coconut-chili beef that's dry, rich, and intensely flavorful.
steps: Blend garlic, ginger, chilies, turmeric into a paste.
Sauté paste in coconut oil; add beef and brown.
Pour in coconut milk, add lemongrass. Bring to boil.
Reduce to low; cook 2.5-3 hours until liquid is absorbed and meat is dark and tender. Stir in toasted coconut.

title: Gado-Gado
description: Indonesian vegetable salad with a rich peanut-lime dressing.
steps: Blanch green beans and cabbage; drain.
Make sauce: blend peanut butter, lime, coconut aminos, garlic, chili, and 2 tbsp water.
Arrange vegetables, sprouts, cucumber, and halved eggs on a plate.
Drizzle generously with peanut sauce.

title: Lomo Saltado
description: Peruvian stir-fried beef with onions, tomatoes, and aji amarillo over rice.
steps: Sear steak in olive oil on very high heat 2-3 min; remove.
Stir-fry onion wedges 2 minutes; add garlic and aji paste.
Add tomato wedges, coconut aminos, vinegar. Return beef.
Toss with cilantro; serve over rice.

title: Aji de Gallina
description: Shredded chicken in a creamy Peruvian walnut-aji amarillo sauce.
steps: Poach chicken 15 min; shred. Reserve broth.
Sauté onion and garlic; add aji paste.
Blend walnuts with some broth; add to pan with parmesan. Simmer 10 min.
Fold in shredded chicken. Serve over rice with egg slices and olives.

title: Moussaka
description: Layers of eggplant, spiced lamb, and a creamy béchamel topping.
steps: Slice eggplant; salt and drain 20 minutes. Brush with olive oil; broil until golden.
Brown lamb with onion, garlic, cinnamon, tomatoes. Simmer 15 min.
Make topping: whisk yogurt, eggs, parmesan, nutmeg.
Layer: eggplant, meat, eggplant, meat. Pour topping over. Bake 400°F 35-40 min.

title: Adana Kebab
description: Turkish ground lamb kebabs seasoned with Aleppo pepper and sumac.
steps: Knead lamb with grated onion, Aleppo pepper, sumac, cumin, and salt.
Form into long, flat kebabs on skewers.
Grill on high 4-5 minutes per side.
Serve with grilled tomato, parsley, and lavash.

title: Turkish Lentil Soup (Mercimek Corbasi)
description: Velvety red lentil soup with cumin, paprika, and a squeeze of lemon.
steps: Sauté onion, carrot, potato in olive oil.
Add lentils, cumin, paprika, and 5 cups water. Simmer 25 minutes.
Blend until smooth. Season with salt and lemon juice.
Serve with a drizzle of olive oil and Aleppo pepper.

title: Shakshuka (North African Style)
description: Eggs poached in a spiced tomato-pepper sauce with cumin and harissa.
steps: Sauté onion, pepper, garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, cumin, paprika; simmer 10 minutes.
Make wells; crack eggs in. Cover and cook 6-8 minutes.
Top with cilantro.

title: Chicken Adobo (Filipino)
description: Chicken braised in vinegar, coconut aminos, garlic, and bay leaves.
steps: Combine chicken, coconut aminos, vinegar, garlic, bay leaves, pepper in a pot.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer covered 30 minutes.
Remove chicken; reduce sauce 5 minutes until thick.
Sear chicken skin-side down in coconut oil to crisp. Pour sauce over.

title: Lamb Mansaf
description: Jordanian national dish — lamb in a fermented yogurt sauce over rice.
steps: Simmer lamb with cardamom and turmeric in water for 90 minutes until tender.
Stabilize yogurt: mix with egg white and cornstarch substitute. Heat slowly while stirring.
Add yogurt sauce to the lamb broth. Simmer gently 20 minutes.
Serve: rice on platter, lamb over rice, yogurt sauce poured over, topped with nuts.

title: Trinidadian Doubles
description: Curried chickpeas wrapped in soft turmeric flatbread with chutneys.
steps: Make dough: flour, turmeric, salt, water. Rest 30 min; roll into small discs.
Fry discs in coconut oil until puffed — 30 sec each side.
Cook chickpeas with curry, cumin, garlic, scotch bonnet until thick.
Assemble: double up two flatbreads, spoon chickpeas in, fold.

title: Yassa Chicken (Senegalese)
description: Chicken marinated in lemon and onion, braised until meltingly tender.
steps: Marinate chicken in lemon juice, garlic, mustard, and salt 2 hours.
Brown chicken in olive oil; set aside.
Sauté onions until very soft and golden — 15 minutes.
Return chicken with scotch bonnet and olives. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: Soto Ayam (Indonesian Chicken Soup)
description: Fragrant turmeric chicken soup with glass noodles, egg, and fried shallots.
steps: Simmer chicken in 6 cups water with turmeric, lemongrass, ginger, garlic — 20 min.
Remove chicken; shred. Strain broth.
Cook glass noodles separately.
Serve broth with noodles, shredded chicken, halved eggs, sprouts, and lime.
